Sentencas: Structure, electrical conductivity and electrochemical performance for a new oxygen deficient perovskite material with composition SrCo0.85Fe0.15O2.62 is explored here.
Titulo: SrCo0.85Fe0.15O2.62-Oxygen Deficient 314-type Perovskite; a Highly Efficient Cathode for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: It crystallizes in a 314-type'' oxygen-vacancy ordered structure (Space Group: I4/mmm) with 2(ap) x 2a(p) x 4a(p) unit cell, and contains alternate oxygen replete [Co2/Fe2-O] and oxygen deficient [Co1/Fe1-O] planes along c-direction.
Titulo: SrCo0.85Fe0.15O2.62-Oxygen Deficient 314-type Perovskite; a Highly Efficient Cathode for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Room temperature Mossbauer spectroscopy and room temperature neutron powder diffraction confirm the presence of mixed valence states (3+ and 4+) for both Fe and Co.
Titulo: SrCo0.85Fe0.15O2.62-Oxygen Deficient 314-type Perovskite; a Highly Efficient Cathode for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Polaronic behavior in the electrical conductivity is observed below 400 degrees C, and attributed to the presence of Co4+ and Fe3+ cations in the structure.
Titulo: SrCo0.85Fe0.15O2.62-Oxygen Deficient 314-type Perovskite; a Highly Efficient Cathode for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The electrical conductivity at 600 degrees C is high enough (similar to 200 S cm(-1)) to act as a cathode material.
Titulo: SrCo0.85Fe0.15O2.62-Oxygen Deficient 314-type Perovskite; a Highly Efficient Cathode for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: At the same time, the polarization resistance measurements show an excellent value of 0.1W cm(2) at 600 degrees C.
Titulo: SrCo0.85Fe0.15O2.62-Oxygen Deficient 314-type Perovskite; a Highly Efficient Cathode for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: These results suggest that at 600 degrees C, this material is a mixed oxide-ion and electronic conductor exhibiting excellent activity for the oxygen reduction reaction, making it a promising cathode material for an intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cell.
Titulo: SrCo0.85Fe0.15O2.62-Oxygen Deficient 314-type Perovskite; a Highly Efficient Cathode for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells
